        <div class="tab-pane fade" id="recovery" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="recovery-tab">
          <div class="accordion" id="recoveryAccordion">
            <div class="accordion-item border-0 shadow-sm mb-3">
              <h2 class="accordion-header" id="recoveryHeading1">
                <button class="accordion-button" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#recoveryCollapse1" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="recoveryCollapse1">
                  What information do I need to provide for recovery?
                </button>
              </h2>
              <div id="recoveryCollapse1" class="accordion-collapse collapse show" aria-labelledby="recoveryHeading1" data-bs-parent="#recoveryAccordion">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  <p>The information required depends on your specific wallet and issue, but generally includes:</p>
                  <ul>
                    <li>Wallet type and version</li>
                    <li>Public wallet address</li>
                    <li>Detailed description of the issue</li>
                    <li>Any partial passwords, hints, or patterns you remember</li>
                    <li>For seed phrase issues: the words you remember and their possible positions</li>
                    <li>When you last accessed the wallet</li>
                    <li>Proof of ownership (transaction history, email verification, etc.)</li>
                  </ul>
                  <p class="mb-0">The more information you can provide, the higher the chances of a successful recovery. Our submission form will guide you through the specific details needed for your case.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="accordion-item border-0 shadow-sm mb-3">
              <h2 class="accordion-header" id="recoveryHeading2">
                <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#recoveryCollapse2" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="recoveryCollapse2">
                  How does the recovery process work?
                </button>
              </h2>
              <div id="recoveryCollapse2" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="recoveryHeading2" data-bs-parent="#recoveryAccordion">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  <p>Our wallet recovery process follows these steps:</p>
                  <ol>
                    <li><strong>Submission:</strong> You complete the recovery request form and provide necessary details.</li>
                    <li><strong>Payment:</strong> You pay the initial analysis fee (or full payment depending on the service).</li>
                    <li><strong>Analysis:</strong> Our specialists analyze your case and determine the best approach.</li>
                    <li><strong>Recovery Strategy:</strong> We develop a custom recovery strategy based on your specific wallet issue.</li>
                    <li><strong>Execution:</strong> We apply specialized techniques and tools to recover your wallet.</li>
                    <li><strong>Verification:</strong> We verify the recovery was successful.</li>
                    <li><strong>Secure Delivery:</strong> We securely provide you with access to your recovered wallet.</li>
                  </ol>
                  <p class="mb-0">Throughout the process, you'll receive regular updates on our progress through your dashboard and email notifications. For more details, visit our <a href="/recovery-process">Recovery Process</a> page.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="accordion-item border-0 shadow-sm mb-3">
              <h2 class="accordion-header" id="recoveryHeading3">
                <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#recoveryCollapse3" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="recoveryCollapse3">
                  What if the recovery attempt is unsuccessful?
                </button>
